# ── Bitwarden Secrets Manager ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Machine account access token. This is the only credential needed at runtime.
# All service credentials below are fetched automatically from Bitwarden on startup.
# Store each credential as a Bitwarden secret whose KEY matches the variable name.
BWS_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Optional: only needed if the SDK cannot determine the org ID from the token
# BWS_ORG_ID=

# Optional: override for self-hosted Bitwarden installations
# BWS_API_URL=https://api.bitwarden.com
# BWS_IDENTITY_URL=https://identity.bitwarden.com

# ── Local development fallback ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# If BWS_ACCESS_TOKEN is not set, the server falls back to reading these
# directly from the environment (or this .env file via dotenv).

# Microsoft Graph (Planner, Entra Admin, OneDrive, Teams, Intune, MS Admin)
# App registration needs: Tasks.ReadWrite, Group.Read.All, AuditLog.Read.All,
#   DeviceManagementManagedDevices.Read.All, DeviceManagementConfiguration.Read.All,
#   DeviceManagementApps.Read.All, ServiceHealth.Read.All, Organization.Read.All,
#   Directory.Read.All, LicenseAssignment.ReadWrite.All
# GRAPH_TENANT_ID=
# GRAPH_CLIENT_ID=
# GRAPH_CLIENT_SECRET=

# UniFi Cloud / Site Manager (api.ui.com)
# UNIFI_API_KEY=

# UniFi Network Controller (UDM, CloudKey Gen2+, self-hosted)
# UNIFI_CONTROLLER_URL=https://192.168.1.1
# UNIFI_USERNAME=
# UNIFI_PASSWORD=

# NinjaOne RMM
# NINJA_CLIENT_ID=
# NINJA_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Microsoft Defender for Endpoint
# Requires a SEPARATE app registration with WindowsDefenderATP application permissions.
# MDE_TENANT_ID=
# MDE_CLIENT_ID=
# MDE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Confluence (Atlassian Cloud)
# CONFLUENCE_DOMAIN=your-org   (i.e. your-org.atlassian.net)
# CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=
# CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN=

# Todoist
# Create a personal API token at: https://app.todoist.com/app/settings/integrations/developer
# TODOIST_API_TOKEN=

# Brave Search
# Get an API key at: https://api.search.brave.com/
# Free tier: 2,000 queries/month
# BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY=

# ── External MCP servers (run alongside this server in Claude config) ──────────
# The following integrations are standalone MCP servers configured separately
# in your Claude Desktop / Claude Code config. They do NOT use env vars here.
#
# Desktop Commander  — npx @wonderwhy-er/desktop-commander
# Filesystem         — npx @modelcontextprotocol/server-filesystem <allowed-paths>
# Obsidian           — requires "Local REST API" plugin in Obsidian (community plugin)
#                      then: npx mcp-obsidian (or the obsidian-mcp package)
# Excalidraw         — npx excalidraw-mcp (or equivalent community server)
#
# See README.md for full Claude config snippets.
